class Solution {
    public int minMovesToMakePalindrome(String s) {
        char[] a = s.toCharArray();
        int n = a.length, res = 0;
        for (int l = 0, r = n - 1; l < r; ) {
            if (a[l] == a[r]) { l++; r--; continue; }
            int k = r;
            while (k > l && a[k] != a[l]) k--;
            if (k == l) {
                swap(a, k, k + 1);
                res++;
                continue;
            }
            while (k < r) { swap(a, k, k + 1); res++; k++; }
            l++; r--;
        }
        return res;
    }
    private void swap(char[] a, int i, int j) {
        char t = a[i]; a[i] = a[j]; a[j] = t;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n²)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Greedy two-pointer sweep: fix the outermost pair by moving the matching character to its mirror position with adjacent swaps, counting each swap. When no partner exists on the right, the lone character must be the middle; swap it once to the center and continue. Guarantees minimal moves by always fixing the outermost pair first.

